column5: Guess you were already gone when I asked.LOL Just getting all duded up and a splash of the Wisers and were gone. Sure hope the Irish Rovers are playing
Probably breakin few rules but why not  Check out Irishfields post in Announcements and Contests .  Another great cause . Maybe a mini GTG pre 'Fishing for Tyler'?  TB
Im thinking we might be a bit late then,in the AM.
Leah and I were talking about this last weekend.  They have put alot of work into it and it sounds like it will be alot of fun.  Brian, you could just have pop
Brian just stay up !
If Wayne does both,Im in.

dang I never look in that section that's why I always say we don't need more sections, when that old discussion comes up here is the link for people who want to know more  http://www.ofncommunity.com/forums/index.php?showtopic=27648
Terry me too ( thanks for the link) found it totally by accident  TB
Thank you, Tinbanger, if that's your real name, and to Terry also.
call me Dave if you must !
Thanks Dave for pushing that into the spotlight.  There is a bar................ and yes 7am will come early... but hell, we're not that old yet are we?
7 am - must be nice to be able to sleep in ! I gotta make coffee for 100 people !  Well not actually , just have to go pick it up .  TB

I hear ya Dave... just think, we have to stay after it's all over to clean up.. then home to Penetang... and then back to Innisfil for 7am!  I posted in the other thread.. but  Doors open at 7PM.. concert starts at 7:30PM... last call is 11:30PM  Leah has about 16 tickets left, so if anyone is ABSOLUTELY sure that you are attending PM me your name(s) and I can leave the ticket(s) at the door for you to pick up on your way in and you can find me inside to reimburse the $20/per ticket. No I don't take Debit.. MC.. VISA or American express! CASH
Last update of the concert poster.

One last bump on this before Friday night in case anyone missed a good excuse to get out on the town. Note there is also a silent auction with MANY great items up for bids during the concert..and door prizes.
Can you clarify on this? I may get the munchies?LOL  Me and the mrs,s are looking forward to this night.

I will as soon as the Mrs. gets back thru the fog from Barrie... she's at a meeting and moving the auction items to the hall...or at least they were supposed to but the basement storage area at the hall is flooded so not sure! Her sister went with her to drive and carry!

Brian... since you're on a health kick.. veggy platters and dip.   ..for me there will be meat and cheese platters and sandwiches !!  Remember these are snacks.. and you are expected to eat before you come! lol  Oh BTW.. the bar is cash only. Silent auction items are cash and they have also made arrangements to take Credit Cards.
I'm sorry I can't make it, I hope you have a great turnout!!!  Maureen
Thanks Maureen... I'll see you Saturday am.
Wayne You got any tickets left Cheryl and I will be there but not till after 8 PM  Gotta get my hair done  TB
Yes Dave... do you want 2 for sure? I need to know before we leave at 2:30 this afternoon and if so I'll pay for them and leave them at the entrance desk.
2 for sure . see you tonight TB
Okay.. they'll be at the door for you. PM me your name and address.. or email it to Leah so they can send you a tax receipt for 1/2 the ticket value.
Email sent TB
